From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alp Lab AB <dev@alplab.example>
Date: Mon, 16 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] flash_map_extended: derive slot base from the alif,mram
 controller reg

On the Alif Ensemble the boot image (slot) lives in memory-mapped MRAM, which
may differ from the memory MCUboot itself executes from: the Secure Enclave
loads MCUboot into ITCM, so CONFIG_FLASH_BASE_ADDRESS describes ITCM (0x0), not
the slot. do_boot()'s vt = flash_device_base() + br_image_off + ih_hdr_size then
points into ITCM (garbage) instead of the MRAM vector table, so the chain-loaded
image jumps to a wild address and faults.

Add an Alif branch (gated on the chosen flash-controller being
alif,mram-flash-controller) that takes FLASH_DEVICE_BASE from the controller's
own reg (0x80000000) -- mirroring the existing nxp_imx_flexspi / st_stm32 arms
that read the controller's memory-mapped reg. Non-Alif boards are unaffected.

Signed-off-by: Alp Lab AB <dev@alplab.example>
---
diff --git a/boot/zephyr/flash_map_extended.c b/boot/zephyr/flash_map_extended.c
index fbddd572..c19b7c66 100644
--- a/boot/zephyr/flash_map_extended.c
+++ b/boot/zephyr/flash_map_extended.c
@@ -46,6 +46,21 @@ BOOT_LOG_MODULE_DECLARE(mcuboot);
 #define FLASH_DEVICE_NODE DT_CHOSEN(zephyr_flash_controller)
 #define FLASH_DEVICE_BASE DT_REG_ADDR_BY_IDX(DT_PARENT(FLASH_DEVICE_NODE), 1)
 
+#elif (DT_HAS_CHOSEN(zephyr_flash_controller) &&                              \
+       DT_NODE_HAS_COMPAT(DT_CHOSEN(zephyr_flash_controller),                 \
+			  alif_mram_flash_controller))
+/*
+ * Alif Ensemble on-die MRAM. The boot image (slot) lives in the
+ * memory-mapped MRAM, which may be a DIFFERENT memory than the one MCUboot
+ * itself executes from (e.g. MCUboot is loaded into ITCM by the Secure
+ * Enclave, so CONFIG_FLASH_BASE_ADDRESS describes ITCM, not the slot). Take
+ * the slot base from the flash-map controller's own reg (reg[0] is the
+ * MRAM memory-mapped base, 0x80000000), NOT CONFIG_FLASH_BASE_ADDRESS.
+ */
+#define FLASH_DEVICE_ID SOC_FLASH_0_ID
+#define FLASH_DEVICE_NODE DT_CHOSEN(zephyr_flash_controller)
+#define FLASH_DEVICE_BASE DT_REG_ADDR(FLASH_DEVICE_NODE)
+
 #elif (!defined(CONFIG_XTENSA) && DT_HAS_CHOSEN(zephyr_flash_controller))
 #define FLASH_DEVICE_ID SOC_FLASH_0_ID
 #define FLASH_DEVICE_BASE CONFIG_FLASH_BASE_ADDRESS
